If you have a long text that needs to be displayed on the ToolStripLabel control, when your form interface is not wide enough, ToolStripLabel will hide all the text instead of using ellipsis to replace the content that is not wide enough.

If no text is displayed, it looks like the entire control is missing.

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.windows.forms.toolstriplabel

Test Code:
.net 6.0

```
namespace ToolStripLabelTest
{
    internal static class Program
    {
        [STAThread]
        static void Main()
        {
            ApplicationConfiguration.Initialize();
            Application.Run(CreateForm());
        }

        private static Form CreateForm()
        {
            var frm = new Form()
            {
                Width = 600,
                Height = 400,

                StartPosition = FormStartPosition.CenterScreen,
            };

            var toolStrip = new ToolStrip();

            var label = new ToolStripLabel()
            {
                Text = "long application message text long application message text long application message text long application message text long application message text",
            };

            toolStrip.Items.Add(label);
            frm.Controls.Add(toolStrip);

            return frm;
        }
    }
}
```

